    <item>
      <title>经济学家称英国应该对离开英国的富人征税</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-07/economists-urge-uk-exit-tax-to-prevent-departures-of-wealthy</link>
      <description><![CDATA[高级经济学家和智囊团敦促财政大臣雷切尔·里夫斯 (Rachel Reeves) 对富人征收“离境税”，每年征收高达 5 亿英镑（6.5 亿美元）的税款，阻止富人离境。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-07/economists-urge-uk-exit-tax-to-prevent-departures-of-wealthy</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 07 Oct 2024 23:01:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>斯塔默向政治低头，任命摩根·麦克斯威尼为首席助手</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-07/who-is-morgan-mcsweeney-and-why-did-uk-s-starmer-back-him-over-sue-gray</link>
      <description><![CDATA[凯尔·斯塔默执政的前三个月过得并不顺利，他的政府饱受捐款争议、内讧和英国公共财政日益低迷的困扰。周日，他终于向工党压倒性胜利的缔造者求助，试图纠正局面。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-07/who-is-morgan-mcsweeney-and-why-did-uk-s-starmer-back-him-over-sue-gray</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 07 Oct 2024 18:54:53 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>里夫斯的税收计划因竞选承诺遭遇现实而受挫</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-07/reeves-s-tax-plans-falter-as-election-pledges-meet-reality</link>
      <description><![CDATA[当英国首相凯尔·斯塔默 (Keir Starmer) 和财政大臣雷切尔·里夫斯 (Rachel Reeves) 策划工党在英国的执政之路时，他们希望通过提高私募股权和超级富豪“非本地”居民的税收来为关键支出计划提供资金。现在，这些承诺正在变成现实。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-07/reeves-s-tax-plans-falter-as-election-pledges-meet-reality</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 07 Oct 2024 18:12:28 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>西班牙银行在暴利税审查后面临额外支付</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-07/spanish-banks-face-extra-payments-after-windfall-tax-review</link>
      <description><![CDATA[审查发现西班牙最大的几家银行少缴了暴利税，因此需要向政府支付额外款项，这可能会影响第三季度的收益。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-07/spanish-banks-face-extra-payments-after-windfall-tax-review</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 07 Oct 2024 15:08:49 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
